Frequently Asked Questions

Q: How does the Fast Hands Trainer Work?

A: The Fast Hands Trainer aims to help users improve their reaction time and hand speed. To set up, the user will tape the numbers 1-5 at different spots on a wall. The Fast Hands Trainer app audibly calls out numbers randomly from 1-5. The user touches the corresponding spot on the wall each time a number is called out. 

Q: Can I vary the amount of time the app will call out numbers?

A: Yes, the user can input the amount of time they would like the app to run for in the input box.

Q: Can I vary the frequency of the numbers being called out?

A: Yes, using the slider, the user can speed up or slow down the frequency of number call outs.



